WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.540 --> 00:00:02.340
- Okay, you're sending an email update

2
00:00:02.340 --> 00:00:03.720
to your close teammates.

3
00:00:03.720 --> 00:00:07.710
You might try opening with,
"HEY, TEAM!" an emoji,

4
00:00:07.710 --> 00:00:10.140
and if your me, maybe
throw in a corny dad joke

5
00:00:10.140 --> 00:00:12.060
to try and keep them engaged.

6
00:00:12.060 --> 00:00:14.640
Now, that same email
might not land so well

7
00:00:14.640 --> 00:00:17.910
with, say, your CEO or a new client.

8
00:00:17.910 --> 00:00:19.680
Kind of makes you cringe, right?

9
00:00:19.680 --> 00:00:22.080
Now obviously messages need to be tailored

10
00:00:22.080 --> 00:00:23.820
to the person receiving them.

11
00:00:23.820 --> 00:00:26.160
Your CEO might just need a
quick bullet-point summary,

12
00:00:26.160 --> 00:00:27.570
but your client, on the other hand,

13
00:00:27.570 --> 00:00:30.990
might need more reassurance
and detailed solutions.

14
00:00:30.990 --> 00:00:33.600
Without help from AI,
crafting several versions

15
00:00:33.600 --> 00:00:36.060
of the same message could take hours.

16
00:00:36.060 --> 00:00:37.980
Not everyone is a professional writer,

17
00:00:37.980 --> 00:00:40.200
and it can be challenging
to adjust your writing style

18
00:00:40.200 --> 00:00:42.030
to different audiences.

19
00:00:42.030 --> 00:00:45.120
It's also pretty common to
get lost in endless rewrites.

20
00:00:45.120 --> 00:00:46.230
All this, and you still need

21
00:00:46.230 --> 00:00:48.780
to make sure your core
message comes through.

22
00:00:48.780 --> 00:00:51.360
Getting your communication
just right is vital,

23
00:00:51.360 --> 00:00:52.740
and that's because you're doing more

24
00:00:52.740 --> 00:00:54.240
than just trying to share information.

25
00:00:54.240 --> 00:00:56.580
You're trying to achieve an objective.

26
00:00:56.580 --> 00:00:59.370
But if someone misunderstands
your message or your tone,

27
00:00:59.370 --> 00:01:01.050
you could lose their trust,

28
00:01:01.050 --> 00:01:03.540
and that can lead to more
questions, more meetings,

29
00:01:03.540 --> 00:01:05.430
and more reviews.

30
00:01:05.430 --> 00:01:07.410
Things can get pretty slow, inefficient,

31
00:01:07.410 --> 00:01:09.033
and draining real fast.

32
00:01:09.900 --> 00:01:11.820
But with Gemini, you
have a writing partner

33
00:01:11.820 --> 00:01:14.670
that can help you produce
multiple tailored email drafts

34
00:01:14.670 --> 00:01:15.950
in just seconds.

35
00:01:15.950 --> 00:01:17.820
In this course you'll learn how to use AI

36
00:01:17.820 --> 00:01:20.520
to amplify the impact
of your communication.

37
00:01:20.520 --> 00:01:22.710
We'll show you how you
can combine your own voice

38
00:01:22.710 --> 00:01:25.680
and judgment with AI's
power to help you generate,

39
00:01:25.680 --> 00:01:28.410
refine, and practice communication.

40
00:01:28.410 --> 00:01:30.330
Of course, the principles

41
00:01:30.330 --> 00:01:32.820
of effective communication
are still timeless.

42
00:01:32.820 --> 00:01:34.410
Things like knowing your audience

43
00:01:34.410 --> 00:01:37.530
and delivering messaging
effectively, they still matter.

44
00:01:37.530 --> 00:01:40.260
But now we can use AI to
deliver on those principles

45
00:01:40.260 --> 00:01:41.463
in a brand-new way.

46
00:01:42.330 --> 00:01:45.900
Specifically your role is to
bring your strategic thinking

47
00:01:45.900 --> 00:01:49.110
and your emotional
intelligence to the table.

48
00:01:49.110 --> 00:01:50.550
Here are five communication elements

49
00:01:50.550 --> 00:01:52.560
where your role is essential.

50
00:01:52.560 --> 00:01:55.080
The first is purpose and intent.

51
00:01:55.080 --> 00:01:57.060
This is all about defining the why

52
00:01:57.060 --> 00:01:59.370
or what you want your message to do.

53
00:01:59.370 --> 00:02:03.240
For example, do you wanna
persuade, to inform,

54
00:02:03.240 --> 00:02:05.283
deescalate, or inspire?

55
00:02:06.330 --> 00:02:09.420
The second element is
understanding your audience.

56
00:02:09.420 --> 00:02:12.090
Only you understand the
priorities of your leadership,

57
00:02:12.090 --> 00:02:14.940
your clients' needs,
and your team's mindset.

58
00:02:14.940 --> 00:02:16.860
Without you, AI won't know the context

59
00:02:16.860 --> 00:02:19.460
and history of your
relationship with your audience.

60
00:02:20.310 --> 00:02:23.250
Next is authenticity and voice.

61
00:02:23.250 --> 00:02:25.350
You wanna make sure that
any communication coming

62
00:02:25.350 --> 00:02:28.230
from you sounds authentically like you.

63
00:02:28.230 --> 00:02:29.340
You're the final editor

64
00:02:29.340 --> 00:02:31.770
that makes sure your message
matches your personal

65
00:02:31.770 --> 00:02:34.080
or company brand and values.

66
00:02:34.080 --> 00:02:35.730
Then there's accountability.

67
00:02:35.730 --> 00:02:37.710
Keep in mind that you're responsible

68
00:02:37.710 --> 00:02:39.210
for the impact your words may have

69
00:02:39.210 --> 00:02:41.670
and any consequences they may bring,

70
00:02:41.670 --> 00:02:44.280
so be sure to read every word.

71
00:02:44.280 --> 00:02:46.680
Finally, there's strategic judgment.

72
00:02:46.680 --> 00:02:48.480
Use your experience and your wisdom

73
00:02:48.480 --> 00:02:51.390
to choose a type of
communication that works best,

74
00:02:51.390 --> 00:02:53.610
like an email versus a phone call,

75
00:02:53.610 --> 00:02:56.280
or in some cases, no message at all.

76
00:02:56.280 --> 00:02:58.650
So what is AI's role in this partnership?

77
00:02:58.650 --> 00:03:00.690
Well, you can use AI as a thought partner

78
00:03:00.690 --> 00:03:03.030
while you build your
communication strategy,

79
00:03:03.030 --> 00:03:06.120
and you can have it tackle
time-consuming tasks.

80
00:03:06.120 --> 00:03:07.050
Let's look at a few areas

81
00:03:07.050 --> 00:03:09.000
where AI can help you reach your goals.

82
00:03:09.000 --> 00:03:10.920
First is brainstorming.

83
00:03:10.920 --> 00:03:12.960
You can describe a communication scenario,

84
00:03:12.960 --> 00:03:15.300
like how to position a
new service for clients

85
00:03:15.300 --> 00:03:17.580
or how to share disappointing news.

86
00:03:17.580 --> 00:03:18.900
Then Gemini can provide you

87
00:03:18.900 --> 00:03:20.430
with options and thought starters

88
00:03:20.430 --> 00:03:23.190
as you evaluate how to
approach the situation.

89
00:03:23.190 --> 00:03:26.640
Next is rapid drafting and variation.

90
00:03:26.640 --> 00:03:30.480
Sometimes the hardest thing
is starting from a blank page.

91
00:03:30.480 --> 00:03:33.390
Within Gemini, Canvas can
create multiple versions

92
00:03:33.390 --> 00:03:36.240
of communication, like business
emails, one-page documents,

93
00:03:36.240 --> 00:03:38.790
and key talking points in seconds.

94
00:03:38.790 --> 00:03:41.730
And it can tailor all of
them to different audiences.

95
00:03:41.730 --> 00:03:43.530
Now we have something to work from.

96
00:03:43.530 --> 00:03:46.410
A third area is refinement and polish.

97
00:03:46.410 --> 00:03:48.390
Gemini can help you improve your message.

98
00:03:48.390 --> 00:03:51.900
It can instantly rephrase
something to make it more clear.

99
00:03:51.900 --> 00:03:55.740
It can also adjust your tone
of voice from formal to casual,

100
00:03:55.740 --> 00:03:59.250
and it can provide feedback
on your work as you iterate.

101
00:03:59.250 --> 00:04:02.400
The last area is practice and simulation.

102
00:04:02.400 --> 00:04:03.840
You can rehearse a sales meeting

103
00:04:03.840 --> 00:04:06.840
or difficult conversation
using Gemini Live,

104
00:04:06.840 --> 00:04:08.580
and this can help you build confidence

105
00:04:08.580 --> 00:04:11.400
before the actual conversation happens.

106
00:04:11.400 --> 00:04:13.740
Now you'll notice that I
didn't list ghostwriter

107
00:04:13.740 --> 00:04:15.510
under AI's responsibilities,

108
00:04:15.510 --> 00:04:18.360
and that's because if you
completely rely on AI,

109
00:04:18.360 --> 00:04:19.770
it might result in communication

110
00:04:19.770 --> 00:04:21.330
that's missing important context

111
00:04:21.330 --> 00:04:23.430
or just doesn't feel authentic.

112
00:04:23.430 --> 00:04:25.380
Remember, you are and
your voice are essential

113
00:04:25.380 --> 00:04:26.880
to the equation.

114
00:04:26.880 --> 00:04:29.880
Instead, you can use AI to
speed up the editing process

115
00:04:29.880 --> 00:04:32.340
to help bring your voice to life.

116
00:04:32.340 --> 00:04:35.130
It can help give your wild ideas structure

117
00:04:35.130 --> 00:04:38.100
or help you get past
that dreaded blank page.

118
00:04:38.100 --> 00:04:39.450
You might spend less time struggling

119
00:04:39.450 --> 00:04:40.950
with how to say something

120
00:04:40.950 --> 00:04:43.830
and more time improving
what you wanna say.

121
00:04:43.830 --> 00:04:45.660
When you use AI in the right way,

122
00:04:45.660 --> 00:04:47.100
you can get closer to the action

123
00:04:47.100 --> 00:04:50.070
or reaction you wanna achieve
with your communication.

124
00:04:50.070 --> 00:04:52.500
You'll find that your
emails actually get read,

125
00:04:52.500 --> 00:04:54.210
and people will follow through.

126
00:04:54.210 --> 00:04:56.040
Or your communication is clearer,

127
00:04:56.040 --> 00:04:59.370
reducing back-and-forth and
getting to quicker decisions.

128
00:04:59.370 --> 00:05:01.470
And maybe your perspective
is better understood

129
00:05:01.470 --> 00:05:02.820
by your teammates or clients,

130
00:05:02.820 --> 00:05:05.880
and as a result, you'll be
more effective in informing

131
00:05:05.880 --> 00:05:08.160
or even changing their opinions.

132
00:05:08.160 --> 00:05:11.580
So let's get rid of those
long, confusing email threads

133
00:05:11.580 --> 00:05:13.443
and start communicating more clearly.